Sokoto State commissioner of health and chairman, state task force on COVID 19, Dr Muhammad Ali Inname has said it’s too early in the day to start thinking of accounting for monies spent on the ongoing fight against the pandemic. Dr Inname who had earlier responded to a question asked by Leadership at Sultan Maccido Institute of Quranic and General Studies during a recent update on COVID 19 situation in the state, said however that, they are very prudent with whatever that have come to them. The elated Commissioner told the cream of journalists then that, the state have started for some days without recording a single case of COVID 19, adding however that, it was not yet uhuru hence no need to celebrate. Though, effort to know how much has the Task Force gotten so far proved abortive, Leadership however gathered that some private individuals, cooperate organizations as well as the federal government have all assisted the state in the fight against the pandemic.